    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-12-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="586"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d586">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Dudley.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 133.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-12-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 29, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of December 8, numbered 188, has
                    been received. The information it gives is of the highest importance. You will
                    please give us additional information, as fast as you can obtain it, concerning
                    the names of the negotiators, buyers, and holders of the bonds of the
                    insurgents. It is desirable to know, if possible, the sums held by each party,
                    and the consideration paid for it, whether in money or supplies and
                    munitions.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>T. H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Dudley</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">United States
                            Consul, Liverpool.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
